------1. Backend Structure

/server
  /models
  /routes
  /controllers
  /middleware
  server.js


-------2. Authentication Routes

Routes:
POST   /auth/register
POST   /auth/login
What they do:
Register
Hash password (bcrypt)
Save user
Login:
Check email/password
Return JWT


---------3. Notes Routes

GET    /notes              (get user's notes)
POST   /notes              (create note)
PUT    /notes/:id          (edit note)
DELETE /notes/:id          (delete note)
Logic:
Only show notes where:
owner_id === user
OR
user is in SharedNotes

--------4. Sharing Routes

POST   /notes/:id/share        (share with user)
GET    /notes/shared           (get shared notes)
Logic:
Add entry to SharedNotes
Store:
note_id
user_id
permission (view/edit)

--------5. GIF Routes (External API)

Using Giphy

GET /gifs/search?q=banana
Frontend calls Giphy directly
Backend just stores gif_url


----------6. Middleware?
authMiddleware
What it does:
Reads JWT from request
Verifies user
Attaches user to request


----------7. Models

User
username
email
password
Note
title
content
owner_id
SharedNote
note_id
user_id
permission
(Optional)

GIFs embedded directly in Note

-----------8. Data Flow (this is what they care about)

Creating a note:
    User sends request → /notes
    Backend verifies JWT
    Backend saves note with owner_id
    Returns note

Sharing a note:
    User sends request → /notes/:id/share
    Backend checks ownership
    Backend adds entry to SharedNotes
    Other user now has access

Adding a GIF:
    User searches via Giphy
    Selects GIF
    GIF URL saved with note